KW  - Principal–agent
KW  - dynamic contracting
KW  - adverse selection
KW  - ratchet effect
KW  - inefficiency
KW  - learning
KW  - path dependence
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA14718
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study a dynamic principal?agent relationship with adverse selection and limited commitment. We show that when the relationship is subject to productivity shocks, the principal may be able to improve her value over time by progressively learning the agent's private information. She may even achieve her first-best payoff in the long run. The relationship may also exhibit path dependence, with early shocks determining the principal's long-run value. These findings contrast sharply with the results of the ratchet effect literature, in which the principal persistently obtains low payoffs, giving up substantial informational rents to the agent.
ER  - 

